                                <h2 class="text-center mt-0">Alessandro Manzoni e <i>I Promessi Sposi</i>: dalle carte
                                    al Web</h2>
                                <p><strong>Italian Cultural Institute in Beijing, March 20, 2025</strong>.
                                    As part of the <strong>Leggo Manzoni/Wo-Dú Manzoni</strong> project, on March 20,
                                    2025, the Italian
                                    Cultural Institute in Beijing hosted a lecture by Professors Giulia Raboni
                                    (University of Parma) and Paola Italia (University of Bologna). The event delved
                                    into Alessandro Manzoni's biography and literary work, focusing on the three drafts
                                    of The Betrothed and their philological development. 
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    Two essential digital tools were presented: the <a
                                        href="https://www.alessandromanzoni.org/">Manzoni Online</a> portal, providing
                                    access to manuscripts, letters, and the author's library, and the <a
                                        href="https://projects.dharc.unibo.it/leggomanzoni/progetto">Leggo Manzoni
                                        platform</a>, a digital environment that illustrate 1840-42 edition with
                                    critical
                                    commentaries and translations. This event marked a significant moment in the
                                    exchange project between the University of Bologna and Peking University, aimed at
                                    promoting Italian literature in China through Digital Humanities and collaborative,
                                    peer-to-peer teaching.
                                </p>
